<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dun</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-14"><hi rend="italic">November 14,
                            1894</hi></date>.<lb/>(Received November 15.)</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Cable instructions received 8tb; answer delayed by the absence of Japanese
                        minister for foreign affairs. He will return to-night; expect answer
                        to-morrow.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>